{{Orphan|date=January 2017}}

'''Gerald A. Danzer''' (born 9 November 1938) is [[professor emeritus]] of history at the University of Chicago. He is a specialist in [[historical geography]], [[world history]], and the use of old maps as historical sources.

==Early life==
Gerald Danzer was born on 9 November 1938. He received his Ph.D from [[Northwestern University]] in 1967 for a dissertation on the subject of "America's Roots in the Past: Historical Publication in America to 1860".<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/18424586 America's roots in the past.] WorldCat. Retrieved 6 August 2017.</ref>

== Career ==
Danzer is professor emeritus of history at the [[University of Illinois at Chicago]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.press.uillinois.edu/books/catalog/63rsf5xx9780252032882.html|title=UI Press - Gerald A. Danzer - Illinois: A History in Pictures|first=Gerald A.|last=Danzer|website=www.press.uillinois.edu}}</ref> where he has taught an MA program for teachers of history for over thirty years.<ref>[https://chnm.gmu.edu/worldhistorysources/analyzing/maps/mapsauthor.html Gerald A. Danzer.] World History Sources, George Mason University. Retrieved 6 August 2017.</ref> He is a specialist in historical geography, world history, and the use of old maps as historical sources. He is a former director of the [[Chicago Neighborhood History Project]].<ref name=ill>{{Cite web|url=http://www.press.uillinois.edu/wordpress/?p=8395|title=Q&A with Gerald Danzer, author of Illinois: A History in Pictures {{!}} Illinois Press Blog|website=www.press.uillinois.edu|language=en-US|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref>

== Selected publications==
